entries.title: Inching forwards - but still not enough votes for Kevin McCarthy to become US House speaker
entries.description: Republican Kevin McCarthy is inching towards securing enough support to become speaker of the US House of Representatives - with 14 more people voting for him in the 12th ballot.

entries.title: At least 29 killed after capture of 'El Chapo's' son sparks violence in Mexico
entries.description: At least 29 people have been killed in Mexico following violent clashes and hours of shootouts prompted by the capture of one of Joaquin "El Chapo" Guzman's sons.

entries.title: Suspect arrested after Kenyan LGBTQ+ activist's body found stuffed in metal box
entries.description: Police investigating the death of a Kenyan LGBTQ+ activist who was found stuffed in a metal box have arrested a suspect.

entries.title: 'Remarkable' recovery: Damar Hamlin's breathing tube removed
entries.description: American footballer Damar Hamlin is breathing on his own and now able to talk following a dramatic on-field collapse.

entries.title: British girl, 13, who disappeared while shopping in Caribbean may have been kidnapped
entries.description: The family of a British teenager who vanished while shopping in the Caribbean have said they are "beyond desperate" to find her as officials investigate the possibility she was kidnapped.

entries.title: Italy bids farewell to footballing genius who gave us tears, screams, laughter and delight
entries.description: Italy knew that Gianluca Vialli was dying, but still his loss has shaken this country profoundly.

entries.title: Former Chelsea player and manager Gianluca Vialli dies aged 58
entries.description: Former Chelsea player and manager Gianluca Vialli has died aged 58 after a battle with cancer.

entries.title: Veteran surfer, one of the 'Mad Dogs', dies riding waves in Portugal
entries.description: Tributes have been paid to a veteran surfer who has died while riding waves in Portugal.

entries.title: 'They were not chess pieces': Senior Taliban leader hits out at Prince Harry over '25 kills'
entries.description: A senior Taliban leader has told Prince Harry that the militants he killed in Afghanistan were "not chess pieces, they were humans".

entries.title: Donald Trump sued over death of police officer after US Capitol riot
entries.description: The partner of a police officer who died following the US Capitol riot two years ago is suing former president Donald Trump.
